Hi Karl.
 > I've been having a problem with CD-Reading under Linux 2.2.x
 > (currently 2.2.3) and was wondering whether anyone could help. I
 > believe it is kernel-related, as there problems vanish when I
 > use 2.0.36-0.7. However, 2.2.x gives some major performance
 > advantages which I'd hate to lose.
There were some serious problems with the CD drivers under 2.2.3 that
were largely fixed in 2.2.4 and fully fixed in 2.2.5. I can confirm
that the performance advantages are still there in 2.2.5 so I would
strongly recommend upgrading from 2.2.3 to 2.2.5 as a cure...
Best wishes from Riley.
